{
  "stem": "8569.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] My sister stayed in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Because she stayed in the ghetto, I had a pass to go back and forth and bring her some food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I also had an opportunity to go back to Hashomer Hatzair.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "What I omitted to say is that when the Warsaw uprising started, the Hashomer Hatzair was very much involved in it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Hashomer Hatzair was-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] was a socialistic movement [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and very Zionistic.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were expert in youth education.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And their whole focus was on Zionism, on Eretz Yisrael.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were taught songs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And no matter what was happening in the ghetto around us, we were kind of protected with the fantasy and the dream of living for Zionism and Eretz Yisrael.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Since of course, any kind of a political activities were banned, they were not only had to cover, but they indeed have created shelters for the orphans whose parents were deported.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they had public kitchens in their headquarters, and they were taking care of all the orphans that they could that were not in the [NON-ENGLISH] place.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, there was no room there for everybody.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they-- this is what the Hashomer Hatzair did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My role in the organization was-- we were organized as a military kind of a movement.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were battalions and-- and small groups of six, seven.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then-- the seven little groups consisted into organization of a bigger group.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was like platoons and whatever the terms are.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My function at first was to teach Polish to the Jewish children who did not know how to speak Polish.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How to read and write Polish.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
